## Context

- Phase 1a-1b, 2a-2b, 3, 5 all complete and committed
- Phase 4 (TCGA COAD/READ validation, task #117) blocked on data download (task #104)
- All modules runnable: crc_common, crc_depmap, crc_dependency, crc_interactions, crc_drug_sensitivity, crc_strategy_matrix
- 63 CRC lines with CRISPR (35 KRAS-mut), 45 in PRISM, 18,435 genes, 6,790 drugs
- Key finding: KRAS itself is top dependency (FDR=0.0001), but per-allele sample sizes (4-8) severely limit power for allele-specific hits
- G12C only had 4 lines (below 5-line threshold), moved to descriptive-only
- No FDR-significant allele-selective drugs or allele-vs-allele differences
- CRC vs NSCLC allele landscape divergence confirmed
- Next: Phase 4 when TCGA data becomes available
